  "intent_precise": "78d33c-part-4.ot2.apiv2: Using Reagents (labware, slot 2), Reservoir (reservoir, slot 5), plate4deg (labware, slot Plate at 4 Degrees C), mag_plate (labware, slot Mag Plate). With temperature module, magnetic module. (1) Pause: Please Refill the 300 uL Tip Box\n                     and Empty the Tip Waste (2) Pause: format (3) Set temperature to temp_mod_setting\u00b0C. (4) Disengage magnets to release beads. (5) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (6) Wait 1 seconds. (7) Transfer 87\u00b5L from source to destination. (8) Incubate for 10 minutes. (9) Engage magnets at height_engagemm height for bead separation. (10) Pause for incubation. (11) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (12) Wait 1 seconds. (13) Wait 0 seconds. (14) Wait 30 seconds. (15) Wait 0 seconds. (16) Disengage magnets to release beads. (17) Pause for incubation. (18) Transfer 22\u00b5L from source (multiple wells) to destination (multiple wells). (19) Wait 1 seconds. (20) Pause: Cover, vortex, spin, incubate,\n        uncover and return the plate. Resume (21) Incubate for 2 minutes. (22) Engage magnets at height_engagemm height for bead separation. (23) Pause for incubation. (24) Pause: Place a fresh 200 uL PCR plate on the temperature module. Resume. (25) Transfer 20\u00b5L from source (A1, A1) to column (0, A1). (26) Pause: Continue to off-deck thermocycler steps and\n     DNA-POST-PCR-2 Post Indexing protocol.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (temp_mod_setting\u00b0C). (volumes 15\u00b5L-250\u00b5L, ~14 min total)",
  "intent": "For this magnetic bead-based protocol, start by refilling the 300 \u00b5L tip box and emptying the tip waste, then set the temperature module to the specified temp_mod_setting\u00b0C. Begin by disengaging the magnets and transferring 200 \u00b5L followed by 87 \u00b5L to your samples, incubate for 10 minutes, then engage the magnets at height_engage mm for bead separation before transferring 50 \u00b5L with appropriate wait times (1 second, then 30 seconds). After disengaging magnets again, add 22 \u00b5L to multiple wells, pause to cover/vortex/spin/incubate the plate off-deck, then return for a 2-minute incubation with magnets re-engaged. Finally, place a fresh 200 \u00b5L PCR plate on the temperature module and transfer 20 \u00b5L from A1 to column A1 before proceeding to the off-deck thermocycler and DNA-POST-PCR-2 Post Indexing protocol.",
